Here's a PlantUML component diagram capturing the static architecture of the Twitter Recommendation System, focusing on the general architectural concern:

```plantuml
@startuml 23fa-cpsc490_canyough

skinparam componentStyle uml2

[Product Mixer] as PM
[Cr-Mixer] as CR
[Follow Recommendations Service] as FRS
[Home Mixer] as HM
[Navi Serving Server] as NSS
[User Signal Service] as USS
[Real Graph] as RG
[Earlybird] as EB
[TweetyPie] as TP
[Manhattan] as MH
[Memcached] as MC
[Strato] as ST

database "Data Sources" as DS

interface "gRPC/Thrift" as GRPC

PM -right- GRPC
CR -up- GRPC
FRS -up- GRPC
HM -up- GRPC

PM ..> CR : uses
PM ..> FRS : uses
PM ..> HM : uses

CR --> NSS : ML serving
FRS --> NSS : ML serving
HM --> NSS : ML serving

PM --> USS : user signals
PM --> RG : graph data
PM --> EB : tweet indexing
PM --> TP : tweet data
PM --> MH : key-value store
PM --> MC : caching
PM --> ST : config & data

DS -- USS
DS -- RG
DS -- EB
DS -- TP
DS -- MH
DS -- MC
DS -- ST

note right of PM
  Orchestrates recommendation
  pipeline components:
  - Candidate Sources
  - Feature Hydrators
  - Filters
  - Gates
  - Scorers
  - Transformers
end note

note bottom of DS
  Abstracted via Storehaus
end note

@enduml
```

This diagram illustrates the general architecture of the Twitter Recommendation System, highlighting:

1. The central role of the Product Mixer in orchestrating the recommendation pipeline.
2. Key services like Cr-Mixer, Follow Recommendations Service, and Home Mixer.
3. The use of the Navi Serving Server for ML model serving.
4. Various data sources and services used by the system.
5. The use of gRPC/Thrift for inter-service communication.
6. The abstraction of data sources through Storehaus.

The diagram addresses the general architectural concern by showing the overall structure, main components, and their relationships in the recommendation system.